What is the structure of my dataset?¶

My dataset consists of 113937 records of loans data with 81 columns of different features starting from the ListingKey which is the Unique key for each listing going through features about the loan , borrower, lender and investors details and these are some of the important features of each:

LOANS --- {LoanOriginalAmount , LoanOriginationQuarter: The quarter in which the loan was originated. Term : The length of the loan expressed in months , LoanStatus: The current status of the loan: Cancelled, Chargedoff, Completed, Current, Defaulted, FinalPaymentInProgress, PastDue. The PastDue status will be accompanied by a delinquency bucket , ListingCategory: The category of the listing that the borrower selected when posting their listing: 0 - Not Available, 1 - Debt Consolidation, 2 - Home Improvement, 3 - Business, 4 - Personal Loan, 5 - Student Use, 6 - Auto, 7- Other, 8 - Baby&Adoption, 9 - Boat, 10 - Cosmetic Procedure, 11 - Engagement Ring, 12 - Green Loans, 13 - Household Expenses, 14 - Large Purchases, 15 - Medical/Dental, 16 - Motorcycle, 17 - RV, 18 - Taxes, 19 - Vacation, 20 - Wedding Loans}

BORROWER --- {BorrowerAPR: The Borrower's Annual Percentage Rate (APR) for the loan, BorrowerRate: The Borrower's interest rate for this loan , EmploymentStatus: The employment status of the borrower at the time they posted the listing, IsBorrowerHomeowner ,IncomeRange : The income range of the borrower at the time the listing was created, prosper score : }

LENDER --- {LenderYield: The Lender yield on the loan. Lender yield is equal to the interest rate on the loan less the servicing fee , EstimatedEffectiveYield ,EstimatedLoss , EstimatedReturn}

INVESTORS --- {Investors : The number of investors that funded the loan , InvestmentFromFriendsCount: Number of friends that made an investment in the loan , InvestmentFromFriendsAmount}

What are the main features of interest in my dataset?¶

I am most interested in the listing category , what types of loans are most applied for ? are they related to certain characteristics about the borrowers ?

Interested too in the lender yield , what make the yield higher ? also loan status, What factors affect the loan status to be cancelled , completed or charged off ?

Finally the investors , What factors makes more investors invest in a loan ?

What features in the dataset will help support my investigation into my features of interest?¶

For the listing category , The loan origin amount and The borrowers details features like employment staus , is the borrower a home owner , income range will have a strong relationship with the types of loans.

For the loan status , The borrower rate , borrower APR , Prosper score of the borrower , LoanOriginalAmount , prosper rating , term and income range of the borrower all will affect the loan status.

Important note: the charged off loans means that their borrowers couldn't pay off their loans and the lender has uncounted their loans in his papers and given up on them leaving them to collection agencies that may collect any of the borrower belongings or properties to pay off.¶

For the investors , I can see The listing category , the lender yield , loan amount and the borrower details features affects the number of investors that may invest a loan.

Q2: What's the distribution of the employment status of the borrowers?¶
In [14]:
#As I'll be using bar charts for many categorical features in the dataset I'll create a function to avoid repetion
def chart_cat(col,x):
    """ Takes a df column and create a decending ordered bar chart of the unique values of the column with seaborn countplot """
    freq = loans[col].value_counts();
    gen_order = freq.index
    base_color = sb.color_palette()[4]

    sb.countplot(data=loans, x=col, color=base_color, order=gen_order);
    plt.title(x,fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90);
    plt.figure(figsize=[8, 5]);
    return plt.show();

chart_cat('EmploymentStatus','Count of borrowers employment status')

<Figure size 576x360 with 0 Axes>
Observation 2:¶

Most of the borrowers are employed and full-timers , interestingly the number of self-employed borrowers is greater than that of part-timers. It's obvious that being employed is a main requirment and factor for the borrower to get a loan.
